Atoms connect to form molecules through bonds. There are mainly two types of bonds:

1. **Ionic Bonds**: This happens when one atom gives away an electron to another atom. The atom that loses an electron becomes positively charged (a cation), and the one that gains an electron becomes negatively charged (an anion). They are attracted to each other because of their opposite charges.

2. **Covalent Bonds**: This occurs when atoms share electrons. Each atom contributes one or more electrons to the shared pair, which holds them together.

